Please enter a search term. Fayetteville’s local news leader KNWA News works closely with trusted Nexstar news partners across the South and Midwest to monitor what’s happening in surrounding communities. Our regional partnerships enhance the impact of our journalism, as we strive to curate uniquely relevant experiences for our local readers in Northwest Arkansas. Stay on top of what’s happening near your family and friends by visiting our news partners in Arkansas, Louisiana, Missouri, Tennessee, Kansas, Iowa, North Dakota, and South Dakota. KNWA News in Fayetteville covers Northwest Arkansas and the River Valley area, delivering the latest breaking news and alerts to issues impacting the local community. Home to Pig Trail Nation, NWAHomepage.com is the top source of sports news in Hog Country. KNWA News is committed to pursuing investigations to uncover wrongdoings and get laws changed to help protect families in Northwest Arkansas. KARK 4 News in Little Rock delivers local news that matters to Central Arkansans, including updates on the coronavirus in Arkansas and Little Rock area weather. Locals count on KARK.com to deliver quick and accurate updates on breaking and state news. KTAL NBC 6 News, KMSS FOX 33, and KSHV 45 covers the Shreveport and Bossier City area including the ArkLaTex region: Arkansas, Louisiana, Texas and Oklahoma. Delivering breaking news, sports coverage, local events, topics and issues that impact the local community. Locals count on Arklatexhomepage.com to deliver and provide accurate and timely weather updates. KTVE NBC 10 News and KARD FOX 14 News in West Monroe, Louisiana covers breaking news, sports, local news, politics, and weather across the ArkLaMiss. For more than 50 years, MyArkLaMiss has been a trusted weather source, being the only station with a Doppler radar in the Monroe/El Dorado area. KOLR10 News in Springfield is the Ozarks’ first source for news, weather, and sports stories that matter most to those who call Southwest Missouri home, including in Springfield and Branson. Sign up for breaking news updates and KOLR10’s daily newsletter from their Murrow award-winning news team. FourStatesHomepage.com in Joplin is the home of Joplin News First, covering community news, weather, and local sports for the Joplin, Missouri and Pittsburg, Kansas areas. During severe weather, including events like the 2011 Joplin tornado, FourStatesHomepage is a one-stop-shop for weather alerts, Joplin radar data, and the latest regional forecast. FOX4 News in Kansas City covers breaking news, weather, and sports for the Kansas City metro area in Kansas and Missouri. Fox4KC.com is your go-to source for the latest on the Kansas City Chiefs and other popular local news topics. Sign up for a FOX4 newsletter to get the best Kansas City stories delivered straight to your inbox. WREG News Channel 3 in Memphis is the leading source for local Memphis news, and works closely with Nexstar news partners across the Mid-South from Tennessee to Mississippi and Arkansas. WREG.com brings you breaking news, hourly and 7-day weather forecasts and radar for the Memphis area. Their team delivers in-depth investigations, Grizzlies news and more for their readers in metro Memphis and beyond. KSN News in Wichita covers the Wichita metro area and points beyond like Great Bend, Garden City, Dodge City, Salina, and Western Kansas. During bouts of severe weather, KSN News is the local authority for accurate forecasts, Kansas radar data, school closings, and other important updates. Subscribe to KSN’s daily newsletter for the top stories of the day. KSNT News in Topeka tells news stories and provides important weather updates for the Topeka metro and Northeast Kansas. Home to Nexstar’s Kansas Capitol Bureau, KSNT.com is Kansans’ source for the most important state news, including timely updates on politics and the coronavirus in Kansas. Subscribe to a KSNT newsletter for the stories that matter most to Kansans. WHO 13 News in Des Moines is Iowa’s leader for local news, weather, sports, and politics. The first Des Moines station to use live Doppler radar, WHO 13 has a long track record of providing accurate and timely weather updates. Sign up here for daily news highlights sent straight to your inbox. WHBF News in the Quad Cities has been serving its four-city community for more than 70 years as a regional pioneer in local news coverage and local weather reporting. WHBF is committed to providing the most comprehensive local news in the Quad Cities, infusing stories with more local context and perspective than their competitors. Visit out OurQuadCities.com for local news, sports coverage, movie reviews, and other compelling content. KCAU 9 News in Sioux City serves more than 400,000 people living on the scenic banks of the Missouri River at the point where Iowa, Nebraska and South Dakota meet. Since becoming the first television station in Sioux City 60 years ago, KCAU 9 has remained dedicated to covering the most important local news, events, and Siouxland weather. KELOLAND News in Sioux Falls has been a local news leader since becoming the area’s first TV station in the 1950s. Those living in Sioux Falls turn to KELOLAND.com first for compelling community content, accurate forecasts and the KELOLAND weather radar, the latest from the South Dakota Capitol, and in-depth investigations on the local issues that matter most. KX News in Bismarck provides local and breaking news, sports, and weather for the Bismarck and Minot communities. Sign up here to get the top Western North Dakota news stories and breaking news updates delivered straight to your inbox. Thanks for signing up! Watch for us in your inbox. Subscribe Now'}]
